'''Rajendra Kumar Anayath''' (born; [[Thiruvegapura]], [[Kerala]], India) is an [[Indian people|Indian]] researcher, educationist and consultant with more than two decades of experience in <ref>{{cite web |last1=Reporter |first1=Staff |title=Named VC |url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-kerala/named-vc/article19339534.ece |website=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=31 August 2018 |language=en-IN |date=24 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=[[The Indian Express]] |title=Meet on printing technology held |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/kochi/2017/jan/15/meet-on-printing-technology-held-1559737.html |website=[[The New Indian Express]] |accessdate=31 August 2018}}</ref> result-oriented research, consulting and training in the global graphic arts industry.<ref>{{cite web |last1=[[The Times of India]] |title=Haryana varsity V-C’s patents on colour coding of clothes|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/haryana-varsity-vcaposs-patents-on-colour-coding-of-clothes/articleshow/63405422.cms |accessdate=31 August 2018}}</ref> Anayath is currently vice chancellor of [[Deenbandhu Chotu Ram University of Science and Technology]] located in [[Haryana]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Printing industry exhibition in Kochi |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/printing-industry-exhibition-in-kochi/article23162110.ece |website=businessline |accessdate=31 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref>
